  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nDev UI log view doesn't catch up with logs after application restart\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1918\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-08-29 at 15 38 46\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0197f62f-b242-4736-b8ba-2861db3921fe\">\r\n\r\nTimestamp difference is reported in https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/42866, DevUI log ends after `Live reload total time: 0.291s` message,  no details about the error. I had to refresh the browser page to see the log with error.\r\n\r\n\r\nScreenshot with more Quarkus app reloads after code change and hitting hello endpoint, no log from the app:\r\n<img width=\"1294\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-08-29 at 15 44 30\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/325f5754-7d7b-4b6b-9394-115d20bd6d65\">\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDev UI log view catches up with logs after application restart\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nDev UI log view doesn't catch up with logs after application restart\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n - Get app from https://code.quarkus.io/\r\n - Run it in dev mode\r\n - Adjust `GreetingResource` to through NPE, e.g. `String foo = null; return \"Hello from Quarkus REST\" + foo.length();`\r\n - Open logs view in DevUI\r\n - hit http://localhost:8080/hello\r\n - Fix `GreetingResource` \r\n - hit http://localhost:8080/hello\r\n - Check logs view in DevUI\r\n\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nmacOS\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nJava 21\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\nQuarkus 3.14.1\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
